
find index of an element in an array
 Linear Search



class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Given array
        int[] arr = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};

        // Element to be searched
        int key = 30;

        // Initialize index with -1
        // -1 means element not found
        int index = -1;

        // Traverse the array
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {

            // Check if current element equals key
            if (arr[i] == key) {

                // Store index when element is found
                index = i;

                // Stop searching further
                break;
            }
        }

        // Print the index of the element
        // If not found, prints -1
        System.out.println(index);
    }
}


ðŸ§  Logic (Short)

Traverse array

If element matches â†’ store index

If not found â†’ return -1

â­ Interview Notes

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(1)

Works for unsorted arrays
